        <methods>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <para>Conducting of field trips.</para>
                </description>
            </methodStep>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <para>Visual registration of an animal/plant/fungus with subsequent identification.</para>
                </description>
            </methodStep>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <para>Georeferencing.</para>
                </description>
            </methodStep>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <para>Organizing of a dataset according to Darwin Core standards.</para>
                </description>
            </methodStep>
            <sampling>
                <studyExtent>
                    <description>
                        <para>The dataset represents records of biota (animals, plants and fungi) made on the territory of Ukraine, Slovak Republic, Uzbekistan and Turkiye in the period from 1996 to 2022 by Mykola Drohvalenko and Oleksiy Korshunov in order to preserve valuable information on biodiversity, collected by Kharkiv specialists, in terms of Russian invasion to Ukraine.
This dataset was prepared (correctly organized according to Darwin Core standards) and published with the help of the project &quot;Preservation of data on biodiversity of Ukraine during the Russian occupation&quot; funded by &quot;Documenting Ukraine&quot; initiative. The initiative is financed by the Institute for Human Sciences in Vienna (https://www.iwm.at/).</para>
                    </description>
                </studyExtent>
                <samplingDescription>
                    <para>Species were identified visually, audially, by remnants of the body or other signs of the species presence in certain place. All identification, recording and georeferencing sessions were made by professional zoologists.</para>
                </samplingDescription>
            </sampling>
            <qualityControl>
                <description>
                    <para>The authors are fully responsible for the quality of data provided within the dataset.</para>
                </description>
            </qualityControl>
        </methods>

